bedroom.Name: Custom Bed Program
bedroom.Body:
Crafted in the USA, our custom order bed program lets you imagine your perfect bed. From fabric choices to headboard height to leg shape and finish, we offer you the ability to create exactly what you want. Each hand crafted order is created with kiln-dried hardwood and every surface is upholstered with your choice of fabric or leather in meticulous detail and tailoring. Exposed feet have a hand applied finish. 

Custom options:
-HEADBOARD STYLE  (Arch, Cut Corner, Flair, Square)
-TYPE  (headboard/footboard, headboard with rails, headboard only)
-SIZE  (twin, full, queen, cal king, king)
-PANEL  (plain front, waffle tuft with buttons, diamond tuft with buttons)
-BORDER  (welted, nails inside, nails outside, double row nails)
-LEG SHAPE & FINISH
-NAIL COLOR 

Please email the store at hello@canvasinteriors.com
or call us at 321-397-9895 to discuss custom design options. 

Pricing determined by options selected, please inquire for current production times.

beds.Name: Custom Bed Program
beds.Body:
Crafted in the USA, our custom order bed program lets you imagine your perfect bed. From fabric choices to headboard height to leg shape and finish, we offer you the ability to create exactly what you want. Each hand crafted order is created with kiln-dried hardwood and every surface is upholstered with your choice of fabric or leather in meticulous detail and tailoring. Exposed feet have a hand applied finish. 

Custom options:
-HEADBOARD STYLE  (Arch, Cut Corner, Flair, Square)
-TYPE  (headboard/footboard, headboard with rails, headboard only)
-SIZE  (twin, full, queen, cal king, king)
-PANEL  (plain front, waffle tuft with buttons, diamond tuft with buttons)
-BORDER  (welted, nails inside, nails outside, double row nails)
-LEG SHAPE & FINISH
-NAIL COLOR 

Please email the store at hello@canvasinteriors.com
or call us at 321-397-9895 to discuss custom design options. 

Pricing determined by options selected, please inquire for current production times.

decor.Name: Geneve Chocolate and Hazelnut Candle
decor.Body:
On the southern tip of Lac Leman lies the beautiful city of Geneva surrounded by the Alps with views of the stunning Mont Blanc. During the 17th century, chocolate making began in Switzerland. World renowned for its quality, Swiss chocolate is often paired with hazelnuts, which give texture to the creamy confection. The classic combination of dark chocolate and toasted hazelnuts creates a complex scent that is bitter without being overpowering. Light this candle, and you will be instantly transported to a Swiss chalet high in the show-covered Alps.

decor.Code: SKU: 3240-LEY216EWP SMALL CANDLE PORTO VECCHIO FIG LEAR & SEA SALT
decor.Name: Porto Vecchio Fig Leaf and Sea Salt Candle
decor.Body:
Honoring the stylish port city of Porto-Vecchio, a natural harbor on the mountainous French island Corsica, this candle is a breath of fresh air. Ordered by the governor of Genoa in 1584, all landowners were required to plant a fig tree each year. With its exceptional sunny and dry climate, Corsica produces some of the highest quality figs in the Mediterranean. Our Porto-Vecchio fragrance boasts a distinctive blend of fresh aromas with top notes of ripened figs followed by a pinch of sea salt which adds a touch of crispness. Let this candle energize and refresh your spirit while it transports you to the warm sunlit shores of the Mediterranean.  

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H

decor.Name: Vienna Espresso and Biscuit Candle
decor.Body:
Nothing is better than a hot espresso when you need a burst of energy. For over 100 years, baristas around Europe have been perfecting the brewing method for the perfect espresso, or as they call it in Vienna, 'kurzer'. Coffee was introduced to the Austrians in the 17th century and now Austria has one of the highest coffee consumptions in the world. Espresso is made to order in 25 seconds and should be consumed quickly. Bring the Viennese café culture to your kitchen as we have preserved the warm aromas of the freshly grounded coffee beans and the lingering smell of sweet cookies.

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H

table-top-accents.Code: 3240-LEY216EWF SMALL CANDLE GENEVA DARK CHOCOLATE & HAZELNUT
table-top-accents.Name: Geneve Chocolate and Hazelnut Candle
table-top-accents.Body:
On the southern tip of Lac Leman lies the beautiful city of Geneva surrounded by the Alps with views of the stunning Mont Blanc. During the 17th century, chocolate making began in Switzerland. World renowned for its quality, Swiss chocolate is often paired with hazelnuts, which give texture to the creamy confection. The classic combination of dark chocolate and toasted hazelnuts creates a complex scent that is bitter without being overpowering. Light this candle, and you will be instantly transported to a Swiss chalet high in the show-covered Alps.  

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H

table-top-accents.Name: Napoli Basil and Tomato Candle
table-top-accents.Body:
Bursting with freshness, this scent captures the world-famous cuisine of Naples. The mouthwatering aroma of the classic Margherita flatbread, consisting of perfectly trimmed basil leaves and sliced San Marzano tomatoes comes to life in this candle. This combination immediately became a favorite in Italian cooking. Transport yourself to the stone laid pedestrian streets of Italy and fill your kitchen with the aromas of the Neapolitan cuisine.  

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H

table-top-accents.Code: SKU: 3240-LEY216EWP SMALL CANDLE PORTO VECCHIO FIG LEAR & SEA SALT
table-top-accents.Name: Porto Vecchio Fig Leaf and Sea Salt Candle
table-top-accents.Body:
Honoring the stylish port city of Porto-Vecchio, a natural harbor on the mountainous French island Corsica, this candle is a breath of fresh air. Ordered by the governor of Genoa in 1584, all landowners were required to plant a fig tree each year. With its exceptional sunny and dry climate, Corsica produces some of the highest quality figs in the Mediterranean. Our Porto-Vecchio fragrance boasts a distinctive blend of fresh aromas with top notes of ripened figs followed by a pinch of sea salt which adds a touch of crispness. Let this candle energize and refresh your spirit while it transports you to the warm sunlit shores of the Mediterranean.  

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H

table-top-accents.Name: Vienna Espresso and Biscuit Candle
table-top-accents.Body:
Nothing is better than a hot espresso when you need a burst of energy. For over 100 years, baristas around Europe have been perfecting the brewing method for the perfect espresso, or as they call it in Vienna, 'kurzer'. Coffee was introduced to the Austrians in the 17th century and now Austria has one of the highest coffee consumptions in the world. Espresso is made to order in 25 seconds and should be consumed quickly. Bring the Viennese café culture to your kitchen as we have preserved the warm aromas of the freshly grounded coffee beans and the lingering smell of sweet cookies.

Dimensions: 3.5 x 3.5 x 3.1H
